               <msContents>
                  <summary>Recto contains the beginning of a letter starting with the basmalla, opening greetings ('may God prolong your life') and a remark about the well-being of the sender's family ('I am writing to you, may [God] prolong [your life, while those with me, are well, God be praised and] thanked'). The letter mentions that the addressee has been appointed over something.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Recto (perpendicular to fibres) contains 8 lines and has a small blank margin on the right side.</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso contains another letter. See nyu.apis.5517.</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Held in the Special Collections Department of Bobst library of NYU and stored loose in acid-free file folders.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
